Wave 8 confirmed Cirrus runs at ~6.4 fps with the bottleneck being SDL3
drawcall overhead (~155 ms/frame from 340 calls × 0.46 ms each). The way
to attack it is to STOP CALLING drawSurface for unchanged content.

This patch fingerprints every drawcall (FNV-1a 64-bit hash of op type,
surface ptr, src/dst rects, alpha, mod color) and compares against the
previous frame's same-index entry. Match + no prior divergence means the
backbuffer at that destination is already correct from last frame — skip
the blit AND don't include that region in the dirty list. First diverging
index forces the rest of the frame to run normally (backbuffer state past
that point is uncertain).

flip() then calls SDL_FlushRenderer + SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects on the
accumulated dirty list instead of SDL_RenderPresent's full-screen
SDL_UpdateWindowSurface — partial flush only covers the changed regions.

Forced full refresh on first frame, drawcall-count delta > 32, clearScreen
color change, and every 60 flips (paranoia coherency check).

Env-var override SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=0 disables the optimization
for debug.

DOSBox-X smoke (title scene + menu navigation + cutscene + lab dialogue
"Sue?"): all visually correct, no corruption. Diagnostic output:
  dirty-rect block @flip=1600..3000: total_calls=430 skipped=430 (99.9%)
  dirty-rect block @flip=3100..4000: 74-89% skipped during lab gameplay

Title-screen idle = 430/430 drawcalls skipped, 3-7 dirty rects covering
3-6% of pixels. Active scene = 74-89% skipped depending on motion.

Predicted real-HW Cirrus impact:
  - drawcall portion 155ms → ~3-15ms (90%+ skipped × 0.46ms each)
  - flush portion 9.5ms (full) → ~1-2ms (small dirty-rect total)
  - per-flip total estimated ~25-30ms for title = 30-40 fps
  - Phase 9 gate of 15 fps: high confidence
